content.description: A crux wide stemming start leads up into a chute.  Some tricky, unprotected moves take you up to a good stance and the first bolt.  Above are three bolts on a steep wall.  From the last of the these three bolts, do a very delicate traverse left into an easier chute.  The fifth bolt protects a 5.9 exit move.
content.protection: five bolts plus one or two stoppers between the first and second bolt, plus gear for an anchor on top
content.location: This climb follows bolts up the largest smooth face on the wall.

content.description: Fun, moderate hand jamming and stemming takes you up past the half way point.  The crack mostly disappears, and a tricky sequence of stemming and intermittent finger jams leads to the top.  The rock is grainy, but the moves are fun.
content.location: To the right of Eat What You Secrete is a bolted face (Red Hot Chili Peppers).  Just to the right of this face is a crack and chimney system.

content.description: Moderate crack and chimney climbing leads to a crux fist crack in a flared chimney near the top.  Rappel off the back side of the formation to descend.
content.location: This crack is near the left end of the formation.  The finish is in a flared chimney.
